definition: Cupid, son of Venus and Mars, Roman god of love and beauty
Belgium/Belgian/abbr. for 比利時|比利时[Bi3 li4 shi2]
to compare/(followed by a noun and adjective) more {adj.} than {noun}/ratio/to gesture/(Taiwan pr. [bi4] in some compounds derived from Classical Chinese)

sentences.english: I hold the Cupid's arrow chasing you, you're wearing a bulletproof vest to fly.
sentences.chinese: 我举着丘比特的箭追呀追，你穿着防弹背心飞呀飞。

sentences.english: Stupid Cupid, stop pickin on me!
sentences.chinese: 无聊的丘比特，不要再找上我了。

sentences.english: Hop a fast train and sit back - Cupid will be waiting for you when you get to your destination.
sentences.chinese: 乘上火车出行吧，丘比特在终点等待你呢。

sentences.english: Her Cupid-bow mouth pouted to give him an airy kiss.
sentences.chinese: 她那丘比特型的嘴一撅，像是要给他送一个飞吻。

sentences.english: God blesses you that you will be shot with Cupids arrow in a short time!
sentences.chinese: 神佑，丘比特之箭会在不久的明天插入你的心扉。

sentences.english: To the Roman's he was Cupid, and his mother was Venus.

sentences.english: Entanglement, meanwhile, is the roping together of particles in order to add more qubits.
sentences.chinese: 而缠结则是编结粒子，以此增加丘比特数。

sentences.english: They're cupids, Mr. Daley. Gods of love.
sentences.chinese: 他们是丘比特，戴利先生，是爱神。

sentences.english: Finally Cupid, who was now healed, longed for her once again.

sentences.english: Her Cupid-bow mouth pouted to give him an airy kiss.

sentences.english: Up to this point, the Christian God has been referred to as Jove.
sentences.chinese: 直到他出现之前，基督上帝都以丘比特的名字来提及。

sentences.english: Jupiter from on high laugh at the perjuries of lovers.

sentences.english: To the Roman's the was Cupid, and his mother Venus.

sentences.english: "See, " said Jupiter, to Venus, "how becomingly she behaves.
sentences.chinese: “看，”丘比特对维纳斯说，“她表现得多得体啊。

sentences.english: Sonny's heavy Cupid face grew red with anger.
sentences.chinese: 山尼那张丘比特式的脸气的涨红了。

sentences.english: Cupid didn’t have enough arrows in his quiver for this pair.
sentences.chinese: 丘比特的箭袋里没有足够的箭给这两个人。
